revision.text:
'''Celia D. Costas''' is a [[film producer]]. She won two [[Emmy Award]]s for the [[HBO]] miniseries ''[[Angels in America (miniseries)|Angels in America]]'' and the [[television film]] [[Warm Springs (film)|''Warm Springs'']] and was nominated for a third Emmy Award for the television film ''[[For Love or Country: The Arturo Sandoval Story]]''. She has also received a [[Producers Guild of America Award]] for ''Angels in America''. She is a member of the [[advisory board]] of the [[Feirstein Graduate School of Cinema]] at [[Brooklyn College]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.brooklyneagle.com/articles/2014/11/28/brooklyn-college-opening-new-graduate-school-cinema-steiner-studios|title=Brooklyn College opening new graduate school of cinema at Steiner Studios|last=Frost|first=Mary|date=November 28, 2015|website=|publisher=''[[Brooklyn Daily Eagle]]''|access-date=August 29, 2016}}</ref>
