{{Benin-bio-stub}}

'''Sukhraj Aujla''' (2 January 1968 – 23 March 2013) was a [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]] folk singer. He became popular after singing songs like ''Nimi nimi tarian di lo'' and ''Rangli Madhani''. He died on 23 March 2013 in a road accident.<ref name=HT>{{cite news|title=Punjabi folk singer dies in road accident|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/Punjab/Amritsar/Punjabi-folk-singer-dies-in-road-accident/SP-Article1-1027830.aspx|accessdate=23 March 2013|newspaper=Hindustan Times|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130320032825/http://www.hindustantimes.com/Punjab/Amritsar/Punjabi-folk-singer-dies-in-road-accident/SP-Article1-1027830.aspx|archivedate=20 March 2013|df=}}</ref><ref name="The Indian Express">{{cite news|title=Singer Sukhraj Aujla dies in road accident, wife injured|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/singer-sukhraj-aujla-dies-in-road-accident-wife-injured/1089679/|accessdate=23 March 2013|newspaper=The Indian Express}}</ref>

