{{Infobox organization | name = Women's Center for Creative Work | logo = Logo Women's Center for Creative Work.jpg | formation = {{Start date|2013}}<ref name="womenscenterforcreativework.com">{{cite web|url=http://womenscenterforcreativework.com|title=WCCW|work=womenscenterforcreativework.com}}</ref> | founder = | founding_location = | extinction = <!-- use {{end date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | merger = | type = | tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = (for European organizations) --> | registration_id = <!-- for non-profit org --> | status = | purpose = | headquarters = | location = [[Los Angeles]], California | coords = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|display=inline, title}} --> | region = | services = | products = | methods = | fields = | membership = | membership_year = | language = | owner = <!-- or | owners = --> | sec_gen = | leader_title = Directors | leader_name = Sarah E. Williams and Kate Johnston | board_of_directors = | slogan = | mission = | website = {{URL|womenscenterforcreativework.com}} | remarks = | formerly = | footnotes = }}
The '''Women's Center for Creative Work''', or WCCW, is a network of women based in [[Los Angeles]] who promote art and feminism.<ref name="LA Times">{{cite news|last1=Carolina|first1=Miranda|title=Grants help Southern California artists make work in the social sphere|url=http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/arts/miranda/la-et-cam-spart-grant-helps-social-practice-artists-20150209-column.html|accessdate=8 March 2015|date=February 10, 2015}}</ref> The WCCW operates through various exhibitions, workshops, dinners, and other special events that connect creative women and feminists. The WCCW was founded in 2013 by [[Katie Bachler]], [[Kate Johnston]], and [[Sarah E. Williams]].<ref name="womenscenterforcreativework.com"/> In 2015, the WCCW received a grant for Los Angeles-based Social Practice Art projects from SPArt.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://spart-la.org|title=SPArt - Social Practice Art|work=spart-la.org}}</ref>
== Events == * [[Wikipedia:Meetup/LA/ArtAndFeminism/LACMA 2015|Art and Feminism Wikipedia Edit-a-Thon]]. Wikipedia meetup. March 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lacma.org/event/art-and-feminism|title=Art and Feminism Wikipedia Edit-a-Thon|work=lacma.org}}</ref> * The Egg & The Eye Pop-up. Afternoon pop-up restaurant with the [[Craft and Folk Art Museum]]. December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Babayan|first1=Siran|title=The Egg & The Eye Pop-up|url=http://www.laweekly.com/event/the-egg-and-the-eye-pop-up-5284534|publisher=LA Weekly|accessdate=8 March 2015}}</ref> * Women Who Run With Wolves. Doll-making workshop with Necessary Habits. August 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.laweekly.com/calendar/women-who-run-with-the-wolves-5018845|title=Women Who Run With the Wolves|author=Tanja M. Laden|work=LA Weekly}}</ref> * A Women's Dinner of Exchanges. Dinner based around ideas of exchange and economies. October 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hyperallergic.com/155236/artrx-la-13/|title=ArtRx LA|work=Hyperallergic}}</ref>
